        {
          "ruleId": "javascript.lang.security.detect-child-process.detect-child-process",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "[CRITICAL] The application directly executes a command string (`req.query.cmd`) received from user input without any sanitization or validation. This allows an attacker to inject arbitrary shell commands, leading to a Remote Command Execution (RCE) vulnerability.\n\nExploit: An attacker can send a request like `/run?cmd=ls%20-la` to list directory contents, or `/run?cmd=rm%20-rf%20/` (if permissions allow) to delete files, or `/run?cmd=cat%20/etc/passwd` to read sensitive system files.\n\nFix: Instead of directly executing a user-supplied command string with `exec`, use `child_process.execFile` or `spawn` where the command itself is hardcoded and only carefully validated user input is passed as arguments. This prevents command injection by treating user input as data, not executable code. This example fixes the vulnerability by forcing the execution of the `echo` command with the user input as a literal argument. For other specific commands, replace `echo` with the intended command and provide appropriate arguments."
