        {
          "ruleId": "javascript.express.security.injection.raw-html-format.raw-html-format",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "[HIGH] User-supplied input (`req.query.q`) is directly embedded into the HTML response without proper sanitization or encoding. This allows an attacker to inject arbitrary HTML or JavaScript code, leading to a Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability.\n\nExploit: An attacker can send a request like `/search?q=<script>alert('XSS')</script>`. When a user visits this URL, the injected script will execute in their browser context, potentially stealing cookies, session tokens, or performing actions on behalf of the user.\n\nFix: HTML-encode all user-supplied input before embedding it into HTML pages. This converts special characters like `<`, `>`, `&`, `'`, and `\"` into their HTML entity equivalents, preventing the browser from interpreting them as code. Using a dedicated HTML sanitization library (e.g., `dompurify`) or a templating engine with auto-escaping features is generally recommended for robust XSS prevention."
          },
          "locations": [
