          "ruleId": "javascript.express.express-fs-filename.express-fs-filename",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "[CRITICAL] The application directly constructs a file path (`fs.readFile(file, ...)`) using unsanitized user input (`req.query.file`). This allows an attacker to manipulate the file path using sequences like `../` to access or read files outside the intended directory, leading to a Path Traversal vulnerability.\n\nExploit: An attacker could send a request like `/read?file=../../../../etc/passwd` to read the system's password file, or `/read?file=../../../../app.js` to read application source code, depending on the application's privileges.\n\nFix: Sanitize and validate user-provided file paths. The fix uses `path.resolve` and `path.join` to normalize the path and then rigorously checks if the resolved path remains strictly within an explicitly defined base directory (`baseUploadsDirectory`). This prevents attackers from constructing paths that reach unauthorized locations on the file system. It's also important to configure appropriate file system permissions."
