        {
          "ruleId": "javascript.express.mysql.express-mysql-sqli.express-mysql-sqli",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "[CRITICAL] The `username` and `password` values from the request body (line 229) are directly concatenated into the SQL `INSERT` query string without proper sanitization or parameterization. This creates a classic SQL Injection vulnerability. An attacker can inject malicious SQL code into these fields, altering the query's intent, bypassing authentication, or executing arbitrary database commands.\n\nExploit: If an attacker sends `username: \"admin', 'pwned'); DROP TABLE users; --\"` and `password: \"any\"` in the request body, the resulting query would become: `INSERT INTO users VALUES ('admin', 'pwned'); DROP TABLE users; --', 'any')`. This would insert a new user, then attempt to drop the `users` table, and the `--` comments out the rest of the original password value, potentially leading to data loss and service disruption.\n\nFix: The query is rewritten to use parameterized queries with `?` placeholders. The `username` and `password` values are passed as an array of parameters to the `db.query` method. The `mysql` driver then correctly escapes these values before inserting them into the query, preventing any injected SQL from being executed as part of the statement. Error handling is also added for robustness."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "src/test-vuln-2.js",
                  "uriBaseId": "%SRCROOT%"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 237
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "The query is rewritten to use parameterized queries with `?` placeholders. The `username` and `password` values are passed as an array of parameters to the `db.query` method. The `mysql` driver then correctly escapes these values before inserting them into the query, preventing any injected SQL from being executed as part of the statement. Error handling is also added for robustness."
              },
              "artifactChanges": [
                {
                  "artifactLocation": {
                    "uri": "src/test-vuln-2.js",
                    "uriBaseId": "%SRCROOT%"
                  },
                  "replacements": [
                    {
                      "deletedRegion": {
                        "startLine": 237
                      },
                      "insertedContent": {
                        "text": "db.query(\n    'INSERT INTO users (username, password) VALUES (?, ?)', // Use placeholders\n    [username, password], // Pass parameters as an array\n    (error, results) => {\n      if (error) {\n        console.error('Database error:', error);\n        res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to create user' });\n        return;\n      }\n      res.json({ created: true });\n    }\n  );"
                      }
                    }
                  ]
                }
