          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "[CRITICAL] The application uses a hard-coded, weak secret (`'secret'`) to sign JSON Web Tokens (JWTs). This makes the tokens highly vulnerable to brute-force attacks or dictionary attacks, allowing an attacker to discover the secret. Once the secret is known, an attacker can forge arbitrary valid JWTs for any user, thereby bypassing authentication and impersonating users. The absence of an `expiresIn` option further means tokens, once compromised, remain valid indefinitely.\n\nExploit: An attacker can attempt to crack the hard-coded secret `'secret'` using tools like `hashcat` or online JWT cracking services. Once discovered, they can craft a new JWT payload (e.g., `{ userId: 1, username: 'admin' }`) and sign it with the known secret. This forged token can then be used to authenticate as the 'admin' user or any other desired user.\n\nFix: JWT secrets must be strong, randomly generated, and stored securely (e.g., in environment variables or a secrets management service), never hard-coded in the codebase. Additionally, JWTs should always have an expiration time to limit the window of opportunity for attackers if a token is compromised."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "src/test-vuln-2.js",
                  "uriBaseId": "%SRCROOT%"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 118
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "JWT secrets must be strong, randomly generated, and stored securely (e.g., in environment variables or a secrets management service), never hard-coded in the codebase. Additionally, JWTs should always have an expiration time to limit the window of opportunity for attackers if a token is compromised."
              },
              "artifactChanges": [
                {
                  "artifactLocation": {
                    "uri": "src/test-vuln-2.js",
                    "uriBaseId": "%SRCROOT%"
                  },
                  "replacements": [
                    {
                      "deletedRegion": {
                        "startLine": 118
                      },
                      "insertedContent": {
                        "text": "const token = jwt.sign(\n    { userId: 1, username },\n    process.env.JWT_SECRET, // Load from environment variable\n    { expiresIn: '1h' }     // Add an expiration time\n  )"
                      }
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
