        {
          "ruleId": "javascript_lang_sql_injection",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "[CRITICAL] The application constructs a SQL query by directly concatenating user-controlled input (`input`) into the query string without any form of sanitization, validation, or parameterization. This makes the application vulnerable to SQL injection, allowing an attacker to manipulate the query to gain unauthorized access to data, modify database records, or even execute arbitrary commands on the underlying database system.\n\nExploit: If an attacker provides `input` as `1 OR 1=1`, the query becomes `SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = 1 OR 1=1`, returning all user records. More maliciously, `1; DROP TABLE users;` could delete the `users` table if the database user has sufficient permissions. Other attacks can include data exfiltration using union-based injections.\n\nFix: SQL queries involving user input must always use parameterized queries or prepared statements. This separates the query structure from the user-provided data, preventing malicious input from altering the query logic, effectively eliminating SQL injection vulnerabilities."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "src/services/userService.js",
                  "uriBaseId": "%SRCROOT%"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 13
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "SQL queries involving user input must always use parameterized queries or prepared statements. This separates the query structure from the user-provided data, preventing malicious input from altering the query logic, effectively eliminating SQL injection vulnerabilities."
              },
              "artifactChanges": [
                {
                  "artifactLocation": {
                    "uri": "src/services/userService.js",
                    "uriBaseId": "%SRCROOT%"
                  },
                  "replacements": [
                    {
                      "deletedRegion": {
                        "startLine": 13
                      },
                      "insertedContent": {
                        "text": "db.query(\n    \"SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?\", // Use a placeholder\n    [input] // Pass input as an array of parameters\n  )"
                      }
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
