            "confidenceLevel": "HIGH",
            "detectedBy": [
              "Bearer"
            ],
            "autoFixable": false,
            "issueId": "CG-031"
          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "javascript_lang_non_literal_fs_filename",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "[CRITICAL] The application constructs a file path using unsanitized user input (`req.query.file`) and passes it directly to `fs.readFile`. An attacker can inject path traversal sequences (e.g., `../`) to read arbitrary files outside the intended directory, potentially accessing sensitive configuration files, source code, or credential files.\n\nExploit: An attacker sends a GET request to `/read?file=../../../../etc/passwd`. The server will attempt to read the `/etc/passwd` file (on Linux/Unix systems) and return its content, disclosing system user information.\n\nFix: Sanitize the user-provided filename by resolving it against a predefined base directory using `path.join` and `path.resolve`. Crucially, verify that the resulting absolute path remains strictly within the allowed base directory using a `startsWith` check. This prevents path traversal attacks by ensuring that no `../` sequences can navigate outside the intended file access scope."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "src/test-vuln-2.js",
                  "uriBaseId": "%SRCROOT%"
                },
